50|$|The {{two largest}} anti-Taliban militias are the mainly Tajik-led Jamiat-e Islami and the Uzbek-led Junbish-i-Milli. Jamiat-e Islami was active during <b>the</b> Soviet <b>war</b> <b>in</b> <b>Afghanistan</b> and <b>the</b> {{following}} civil <b>war</b> <b>in</b> <b>Afghanistan.</b> Junbish-i-Milli was also involved <b>in</b> <b>the</b> civil <b>war</b> <b>in</b> <b>Afghanistan.</b> Both groups {{were members of}} the anti-Taliban Northern Alliance.|$|R
